{{Infobox organization | name = NHS Employers | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = | logo_size = | logo_caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = 2004 <!-- use {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | founder = | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} --> | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = Chief Executive | leader_name = Danny Mortimer | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = | staff_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = {{URL| http://www.nhsemployers.org}} | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }} '''NHS Employers''' is an organisation which acts on behalf of [[NHS trust]]s in the [[National Health Service]] in [[National Health Service (England)|England]] and [[NHS Wales|Wales]]. It was formed in 2004, is part of the [[NHS Confederation]], and negotiates contracts with healthcare staff on behalf of the government.
==History== In January 2004 the [[Department of Health (UK)|Department of Health]] announced the responsibility for negotiating staff terms and conditions was to be devolved by them to the NHS Confederation.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.publicfinance.co.uk/news/2004/01/nhs-take-over-staff-pay-negotiations |title=NHS to take over staff pay negotiations |work=[[Public Finance (magazine)|Public Finance]] |date=8 January 2004 |accessdate=2 January 2016}}</ref> In November 2004 NHS Employers was formed,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2004/nov/09/health.politics1 |title='Poison chalice' warning to NHS pay body |first=Hélène |last=Mulholland |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=9 November 2004 |accessdate=2 January 2016}}</ref> and became the body that negotiates healthcare staff contracts on behalf of the government.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-34383670 |title=Health secretary to meet doctors over contract row |work=[[BBC News]] |date=28 September 2015}}</ref> They regularly collect and analyse the views of employers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nhsemployers.org/about-us |title=About us |work=NHS Employers |accessdate=2 January 2016}}</ref>
In September 2014, Danny Mortimer was named Chief Executive of NHS Employers, succeeding Dean Royles.<ref name="HR mag 12Sep2014">{{cite news |url=http://www.hrmagazine.co.uk/article-details/mortimer-named-nhs-employers-ceo |title=Mortimer named NHS Employers CEO |first=Arvind |last=Hickman |work=HR Magazine |date=12 September 2014 |accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref>
==Initiatives== In 2005, most NHS trusts estimated that around half of their staff were suffering from workplace stress, but less than a third of health service managers that responded were able to say that their trusts had a stress management policy at the time.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/4399930.stm |title=NHS staff stress rife, bosses say |work=BBC News |date=2 November 2005}}</ref>
In 2012 they launched a ''Speaking Up Charter'', asking [[NHS trust]]s to commit to actions that would help staff to raise concerns.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-31362196 |title=NHS 'to get whistleblower guardians’ |first=Nick |last=Triggle |work=BBC News |date=11 February 2015}}</ref>
In June 2014 they published statistics highlighting the proportion of women in various sections of the NHS workforce.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independentnurse.co.uk/news/nhs-employers-publishes-gender-statistics/64414 |title=NHS Employers publishes gender statistics |first=Alex |last=Turnbull |work=Independent Nurse |date=2 June 2014 |accessdate=2 January 2016}}</ref>
