{{for|the women's lifestyle magazine|Women's Health (magazine)}} {{for|the other academic journal of a similar name|Journal of Women's Health}} {{Infobox journal | title = Women's Health Issues | cover = | discipline = [[Women's health]], [[women's studies]] | abbreviation = Women's Health Issues | editor = Chloe E. Bird | publisher = [[Elsevier]] on behalf of the [[Jacobs Institute of Women's Health]] | country = United States | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1990–present | impact = 1.811 | impact-year = 2015 | website = http://www.whijournal.com/ | link1 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/10493867 | link1-name = Online archive | link2 = http://www.elsevier.com/locate/issn/10493867 | link2-name = Journal page at publisher's website | ISSN = 1049-3867 | eISSN = 1878-4321 | OCLC = 222770672 | LCCN = 91656026 | CODEN = WHISEH }} '''''Women's Health Issues''''' is a bimonthly [[peer-reviewed]] [[medical journal]] covering women's health care and policy. It is the official journal of the [[Jacobs Institute of Women's Health]] and published on their behalf by [[Elsevier]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Chloe E. Bird ([[RAND Corporation]]).<ref name=Journal_info>{{cite web |title=Women's Health Issues |url=http://www.journals.elsevier.com/womens-health-issues#journalscope |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.htdiary.com/category/health-issues/|title=HEALHT ISSUES Archives - Health Diary|website=Health Diary|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref>
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in: {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| * [[Cumulative Index to Nursing and Allied Health Literature]] * [[Current Contents]] * [[MEDLINE]] * [[Embase]] * [[Sociological Abstracts]] * Studies on Women Abstracts * [[Scopus]] }} According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2015 [[impact factor]] of 1.811, ranking it 4th out of 40 journals in the category "Women's Studies".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Women's Studies |title=2015 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
